## Analysis Notes
### Shorts 1 (kAOMa_aiM34) - "Tube Lens" (Review Channel)
- Transitions: Quick cuts between a character/host and screen recordings.
- Text Animation: Bold white text with black outlines. High visibility.
- Color Grading: Vibrant, high contrast.
- Audio/SFX: Fast-paced narration, energetic background music.

### Shorts 2 (7a6F98ZCZ_0) - "Nutricore" (Brand/Product)
- Transitions: Smooth zooms and stylized transitions between benefit slides.
- Text Animation: Massive, colorful, stylized fonts (Pink/Cyan/White). Dynamic placement.
- Color Grading: Thematic (Dark blue for sleep product), professional product lighting.
- Audio/SFX: Likely persuasive VO with thematic SFX.

### Shorts 3 (LEmBOUtD-TQ) - "In a Minute" (Aesthetic Ads)
- Transitions: Cinematic match cuts, smooth pans, slow zooms.
- Text Animation: Minimalist, elegant, clean typography.
- Color Grading: Warm, aesthetic, high-end "lifestyle" look.
- Audio/SFX: High-quality ASMR SFX (liquid pouring), chill BGM.

## Technical Gaps (Top 5)
1. **Dynamic Visual Rhythm**: The old video used static images. High-performing Shorts use 1.5-2s cuts and Ken Burns zooms.
2. **Typography & Layout**: Old video had screen-filling generic text. Needs bold, modern fonts with intentional placement (not blocking the product).
3. **POV & Authenticity**: Generic renders vs. hands-on/POV clips. Must use clips that show the product in action.
4. **Audio-Visual Sync (SFX)**: Old video lacked ASMR/impact SFX. Every action needs a corresponding sound (click, slice, pop).
5. **Color/Mood Grading**: Old video was flat. Needs professional grading (High contrast or Warm aesthetic) to look "expensive".

## Improvement Plan (Luna v5.5 Ultimate)
- **Visuals**: 
    - Implement a "1.5-second rule" for cuts. No clip stays static.
    - Apply automatic Ken Burns (zoom-in/out) to all images.
    - Focus on POV (Point of View) angles to simulate user experience.
- **Audio**:
    - Add "Impact SFX" for every text pop-up and "ASMR SFX" for product actions (e.g., the sound of a grinder).
    - Sync background music BPM with scene transitions.
- **Text**:
    - Use "Black Han Sans" or "Pretendard Bold" for a professional look.
    - Use contrasting highlight colors (Yellow on Black, White on Dark Blue).
    - Position text in the "Safe Zone" (middle/top) to avoid being covered by UI elements.
- **Color**: 
    - Boost saturation by 15-20% and add a slight vignette to focus on the product.
    - Grade each video based on category (Warm for Food, High-Contrast for Gadgets).
- **Strategy**:
    - **Hook**: First 1.5s must show the "Solution" or "Shocking Result".
    - **Monetization**: Use "Urgency-based" pinned comments instead of plain links.
